@Aquaxi

As stated in the release notes, non-AVCHD/Blu-ray drives will write the movie image to a DVD disc, but they will not autorun it - only a compatible player will, although of course, you can play the .m2ts video file from the BDMV/STREAM folder, as long as you have the correct codecs installed.

Glad you enjoyed it - it's a crackin' movie. =)
